case_body_condition: Not recognizable - Partial remains with soft tissues
case_circumstances: Male torso with fragmented skull (no mandible or teeth present) was found on March 10, 1977 30 miles off the coast of Point Judith and hauled up by a fisherman. Comparisons were made with multiple missing persons at the time however none were determined to be this person. Body was released for burial by Anderson Winfield Funeral Home in 1992. A .22 caliber bullet was located in the upper left hip but it was undetermined if this injury happened perimortem or antemortem.
